    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-10T11:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-10T11:37:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <head>124. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station</gloss> in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >place not declassified</hi>]<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d124fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79-01025A, Box 8, Folder 9.
                        Secret; Priority. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_WFHSW1"
                        >Wisner</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                            >PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in Florida.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-04-10T16:37:00+00:00">April 10, 1954, 1637Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>46015. Re: <gloss target="#t_DIR1">DIR</gloss> 45998.<note n="2" xml:id="d124fn2">
                        <ref target="#d123">Document 123</ref>.</note> For <gloss
                        target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_WHS1"
                        >Whiting</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>High level meeting referred to in ref scheduled for this afternoon
                            following which <gloss target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss> will receive
                            further guidance.<note n="3" xml:id="d124fn3">On April 10 <persName
                                    corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName> briefed Assistant
                                Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName> on <gloss
                                    target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> and <persName
                                    corresp="#p_HHF1">Holland</persName>, shocked by security
                                lapses, demanded a top-level review of the project. (Cullather,
                                Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> p. 101)
                                See <ref target="#d127">Document 127</ref> for <gloss
                                    target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>’s response.</note> However in
                            meanwhile <persName corresp="#p_WHS1">Whiting</persName> requested by
                                <persName corresp="#p_STARKE1">Starke</persName> convey to <gloss
                                target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss> following personal message.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“<gloss target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss> should not have any
                                further direct contact with local authorities or other non <gloss
                                    target="#t_ODYOKE1">ODYOKE</gloss> individuals with regard to
                                any aspect of Success except pursuant to and within limits of
                                specific instructions and authorization from HQs <gloss
                                    target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> and <gloss
                                    target="#t_KUBARK1">KUBARK</gloss>. <persName
                                    corresp="#p_STARKE1">Starke</persName> very concerned with
                                regard present extent official exposure and considers that this
                                raises serious question desirability continuing operation as
                                previously planned.”</p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In light of the foregoing and without in any way purporting to prejudge
                        outcome of basic policy decision re continuation and timing success
                            <persName corresp="#p_WHS1">Whiting</persName> suggests <gloss
                            target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss> may wish consider and offer
                        recommendations concerning best means softening impact local authorities
                            <gloss target="#t_SKILLET1">SKILLET</gloss>’s withdrawal from direct
                        contact. Realize possibility they <pb facs="0263" n="233" xml:id="pg_233"/>
                        may interpret such breakoff as evidence complete reversal <gloss
                            target="#t_ODYOKE1">ODYOKE</gloss> position regarding all aspects this
                        matter. Also on assumption policy decision may favor continuation project in
                        something like present form recommendations <gloss target="#t_SKILLET1"
                            >SKILLET</gloss> and <persName corresp="#p_PSD1">Princep</persName> for
                        re-establishment indirect channels communication will be needed for
                        consideration here.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
